ing a hat, partially visible behind him. The open side windows give a clear view of the roomy interior and the occupants’ upright, relaxed posture.\n\nFinally, the car returns to the showroom setting. The light-colored Chevrolet is again centered among other display cars. The suited man in the fedora walks toward it and stands beside the driver’s side, facing the vehicle. Large bold lettering appears high across the wall above the car: “’57 CHEVROLET.” The final image holds the car as the main object, with the man standing close by as if concluding his inspection at the dealership.",
